This paper is about sound event detection using neural networks, which falls under the subfield of audio signal processing. The paper also mentions the use of virtual adversarial training and self-adaptive label refinement, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
